OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FHe said: "But the crown accepts that
OL,8,Fthis defendant is not at fault for
OL,9,Fthat collision because he could not
OL,10,Fhave expected a pedestrian to have
OL,11,Fbeen crossing the M62 or reacted to
OL,12,Favoid the collision."
OL,14,FMr Smith also conceded that the
OL,15,Fmotorway at the point of the
OL,16,Fcollision, near the Hartshead Moor
OL,17,Fservices, Bradford, is "perhaps
OL,18,Fincorrectly called" a smart motorway,
OL,19,Fwith no hard shoulder.
OL,26,@oD@JOUtD@UO]yD@XOUzD@SO]
